Here are three hypotheses in natural language that we can use to investigate the process:

**Hypothesis 1:** "The Review request activity is always completed before the Calculate terms activity."

This hypothesis can be tested by analyzing the sequence of events in the process and checking if the Review request activity always precedes the Calculate terms activity.

**Hypothesis 2:** "The Prepare special terms activity is only executed when the Standard terms applicable? gateway condition is false."

This hypothesis can be tested by analyzing the decisions made at the Exclusive Gateway and checking if the Prepare special terms activity is only executed when the condition is false.

**Hypothesis 3:** "The Send quote activity is always the last activity executed in the process before the End (Quote sent) event."

This hypothesis can be tested by analyzing the sequence of events in the process and checking if the Send quote activity always precedes the End (Quote sent) event.

These hypotheses are specific and simple, making them easy to convert into SQL queries to test them against the event log data.
